<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.263446>
    dc:description "PLATE 146. Splendrillia bartschi (Haas, 1941). Upper panel. Fig. 1: holotype, Argus Bank, Bermuda (FMNH 13672). Photograph courtesy of Mr. Jochen Gerber of the FMNH; color not true. Figs. 2 – 3: specimens from near North Rock, Bermuda (H. G. Lee coll.). Lower panel. Figs. 4, 6: specimen from near North Rock, Bermuda (USNM 1291357). Fig. 4: ventral, lateral & dorsal views; Fig. 6: apical view, V = varix, L = edge of outer lip. Fig. 5: enlarged view of the juvenile with a better view of the protoconch (not to scale), Somerset Pt.: 9.7 km N of boatyards (H. G. Lee coll.)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/263446/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

